doc.after: Although originally designed for the L-1011-1, Rolls-Royce knew that the RB211 could be developed to provide greater thrust. The new version, which first ran on 1 October 1973,[15] was designated RB211-524, and would be able to power new variants of the L-1011, as well as the Boeing 747.
